thanks to a rainstorm two broken radio 
beacons and a pilot who didnt want to take chances pope john paul 
ii got a glimpse of the one country he was trying to avoid during 
his tour of southern africa 
in his next unplanned adventure wednesday the 68yearold 
pontiff was escorted by soldiers and police on an improvised 
270mile drive from south africa to lesotho where a bus hostage 
drama was unfolding at the site of the high point of his pilgrimage 
the popes strange odyssey began 75 minutes after takeoff from 
gaborone botswana when the air zimbabwe boeing 707 taking him to 
tiny lesotho an enclave surrounded by south africa gave up 
efforts to land at the airport in maseru 
circling and bumping in clouds so thick they covered the 
wingtips the airliner carrying reporters and the papal party 
veered west at 7600 feet over maseru and climbed back to cruising 
altitude 
its johannesburg announced vatican spokesman joaquin 
