<TEXT>
the international olympic committee 
today awarded the 1994 winter games to the norwegian city of 
lillehammer dashing us hopes of hosting the games in anchorage 
alaska 
in the norwegian city of 22000 people danced in the streets 
and were served free breakfast along the main street as they 
celebrated the announcement 
this is an enormeous challenge for all norway and especially 
for lillehammer and the districts around said prime minister gro 
harlem brundtland in oslo 112 miles away 
lillehammer has been given a preliminary budget of 312 million 
to stage games the norwegian government said 
the announcement was made by ioc president juan antonio 
samaranch following a vote by members of the organization 
lillehammer will become the second norwegian city to host the 
winter games oslo organized the 1952 games 
mrs brundtland of norway was in seoul this week lobbying for 
lillehammer among members of the ioc she called norway the 
cradle of winter sports and praised lillehammers compact 
sports center 
sofia bulgaria had been widely expected to be chosen as the 
first east bloc nation to hold the games based on the strong 
support from its allies 
anchorage and ostersund sweden were the other contenders for 
1994 
when samaranch made his announcement following a vote by the 
86member body a group of norwegian representatives in the crowd 
shouted in joy and waved their countrys flag 
lillehammer is the smallest of the contending cities and is 
located on lake mjoesa norways largest lake 
the city has already begun building a sports center that offers 
compact facilities that will not necessitate extensive travel by 
competing teams 
the ioc voted in 1986 to stagger the winter and summer olympics 
and lillehammer will be the first to host the new onceintwoyears 
cycle 
sweden submitted a bid the last four times for the winter games 
and the country has tried 12 times in all to be a winter olympics 
host 
the four cities made their final presentations wednesday using 
speeches films and slide shows to try to convince the ioc that 
their bid was best anchorage lillehammer and sofia all were 
losers two years ago when albertville france was awarded the 
winter games for 1992 
