only power money and process contradicts examples of reforms cited 
in the report in school systems in dade county rochester toledo 
and pittsburgh 
the idea that innovative education reform initiatives in 
rochester and miami could have taken place without the strong 
backing of local aft affiliates or a strong contract is just plain 
wrong shanker said 
he called collective bargaining the best way for communicating 
between teachers and school administrators because it insures 
that whatever dialogue occurs is held on equal ground 
the associations report said the two major themes surfacing in 
several recent calls for education reform are restructuring schools 
and empowerment of teachers 
but it defines empowerment as sharing information not 
power with teachers designing instructional programs in 
cooperation with them and assigning them a share of the 
responsibility for fostering excellence 
