<TEXT>
six people died when hurricane gilbert 
the strongest storm on record battered the yucatan peninsula and 
left this city on thursday littered with boats and seaweed hundreds 
of yards from shore 
along the northern mexican gulf coast authorities evacuated 
fishing villages and towns as gilbert churned in that direction 
with 120 mph winds on wednesday morning when the hurricane 
slammed into the caribbean resort of cancun winds topped 160 mph 
the storm left much of yucatan without communication 
electricity or drinking water airports were shut most roads were 
blocked and supplies were running low campeches governor declared 
the state a disaster area thursday afternoon and appealed for 
relief supplies 
thousands of tourists in resort areas were stranded many 
surviving on cookies and milk handed out in shelters 
in campeche the state capital on the peninsulas west coast 
