judaism said the forthcoming presidential election involves the 
economy human rights and defense and urged jews to vote in it 
rabbi moses a birnbaum president of the new york board of 
rabbis says jews have always cherished one ideal the 
obligation upon us literally to repair the world the vision of 
a world healed by us 
as we wish each other life let us wish each other the courage 
and strength to turn the vision into reality he said 
citing the recurrent prayer at holiday services inscribe us 
into the book of life o you who delight in life birnbaum said 
no prayer is more important for jews and all humankind 
but we live in days when life is often cheap more often 
corroded by cynicism and corruption we see if we have the 
courage to look so many countless lives made unlivable by poverty 
and disease and homelesness 
we see if we do not turn away lives inflamed by prejudice 
and hatred and fantaticism we witness millions of lives snuffed 
out by senseless wars and bloody persecution 
he said surmounting these antilife conditions demands not only 
prayer but our unflagging determination to work for justice and 
equality for all gods children 
