<TEXT>
from the first they have been styled the great debates 
libraries of briefing books hours of cram courses and rehearsals 
have gone into them for all of that they have produced neither 
great oratory nor breakthroughs on major issues instead they have 
offered televised summations of the standard speeches and positions 
the candidates serve up daily in their campaign travels and some 
have turned on mistakes in style or substance 
the major impact on those campaigns has been one of impressions 
rather than of words a haggard nixon his lateday beard darkening 
his cheeks a fumbling gerald r ford a defensive jimmy carter a 
rambling ronald reagan his age apparently showing 
those impressions tended to take shape after the debates in 
reflection rather than in the performance 
reagan was 73 during his last reelection campaign age became 
an issue after an uncharacteristically fumbling tv performance in 
louisville ky against walter f mondale it never was mentioned 
directly in that debate when it was in a second debate in kansas 
city reagan punctured it with a wisecrack that worked an age 
problem no said reagan i am not going to exploit for political 
purposes my opponents youth and inexperience 
the era of the televised debate began in chicago on sept 26 
1960 nixon versus kennedy nixon then vice president held a 
narrow lead in the polls and overruled some of his advisers to 
debate the lesserknown kennedy 
nothing either man said counted nearly as much as the way nixon 
looked that night hed used powder to cover his beard it streaked 
as he perspired in the hot tv lights kennedy looked trim and fit 
small screen black and white television magnified the images that 
debate first of four gave kennedy a lasting lift and he won a 
hairbreadth election 
the debates were said to have created a tradition future 
candidates surely would follow none did for 16 years 
president lyndon b johnson wasnt interested in giving his 
republican challenger the equal billing of a debate in 1964 when 
the polls anticipated his landslide election barry goldwater the 
republican nominee excused him in advance saying a president 
shouldnt debate because he might just slip and say something 
inadvertently that could change the course of history 
nixon was the republican nominee in 1968 and again in 1972 he 
was the favorite and hed learned his lesson about debating 
but in 1976 ford president by appointment and lagging behind 
carter needed a jump start for his campaign he sought it with a 
debate challenge he and carter met three times and ford made one 
magnified mistake in the second debate he said there is no 
soviet domination of eastern europe and there never will be under a 
ford administration pressed by a questioner he insisted on it 
eventually he corrected the statement but it hurt perhaps not 
so much for content as for the way it fit the snide claims of 
fords critics that he was prone to err and bumble 
carter said later that he wouldnt have won without the debates 
four years later carter was the underdog pressing for 
oneonone debates with republican reagan they finally met in 
cleveland one week before the election that was the night a 
relaxed reagan in his element played the longsuffering victim 
whenever carter attacked there you go again he would say 
