the decline to 26658 billion in the sevenday period ended 
wednesday followed a 2413 million drop in the funds assets the 
previous week according to the washingtonbased mutual fund trade 
group 
the funds assets hit a record high 28002 billion in the week 
ended feb 24 
the investment company institute said that in the latest week 
assets of 223 general purpose funds fell 535 million to 8492 
billion assets of 103 brokerdealer funds fell 1275 million to 
1131 billion and assets of 126 institutional funds fell 1664 
million to 6856 billion 
the sevenday average yield on money market mutual funds in the 
week ended tuesday to 739 percent from 737 percent the previous 
week according to donoghues money fund report a trade journal 
based in holliston mass 
the 30day average yield rose to 731 percent from 723 percent 
donoghues said 
the average maturity of the portfolios held by money funds was 
34 days from 33 days donoghues said 
separately the newsletter bank rate monitor said its survey of 
100 leading commercial banks savings and loan assocations and 
savings banks in the nations 10 largest markets showed the 
effective annual yield available on money market accounts rose to 6 
percent as of wednesday from 597 percent a week earlier 
the north palm beach flabased newsletter said the effective 
annual yield available on special savings accounts called super 
now accounts were unchanged at 512 percent 
